# CSS Positioning

Positioning controls where elements appear on a page.

## Static

Default positioning.

```css
div {
    position: static;
}
```

## Relative

Moves relative to its original position.

```css
div {
    position: relative;
    top: 20px;
}
```

## Absolute

Positions relative to nearest positioned parent.

```css
div {
    position: absolute;
    right: 10px;
}
```

## Fixed

Remains fixed during scrolling.

```css
header {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
}
```

## Sticky

Switches between relative and fixed.

```css
nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
}
```

## Real-World Example

Sticky navigation bars improve user experience.

## Summary

Positioning is essential for creating advanced layouts.
